(A) Evidence of erosion and silting. Give extent or percent of stream bed affected:
(B) Particulars of scouring of spawning beds or change in course of stream :
Small amount of new blowdown again at start of reds at cnr. at 600 m.
(C) Water levels flow, normal, abnormal. If abnormal, details should be given :
Consistently good water levels through the spawning period.
(D) Particulars of distribution of salmon over stream bed :
Chums and Pinks spread to lake, but light utilization of upper 500 m. from chums
High predatation from bears, 2 new cubs seen in the system this year.
(F) Evidence of digging up eggs by late spawning fish :
The new blowdown is not a problem at this time.
COMMENTS ON ANY OTHER CONDITIONS AFFECTING THIS STREAM
No test fishing in Darwin Sound this year. Good seed of pinks but very poor chum return. The last walk was too early for an accurate final count.
